content.text: From the list of numbers, write down
A train journey starts at 23 30 and finishes at 07 15 the next day
Find the time taken for this journey
Find the actual distance between town \(K\) and town \(L\)
Measure the bearing of town \(L\) from town \(K\)
The scale drawing shows the positions of town \(K\) and town \(L\)
Each student in a class of 20 students records the number of coins in their pockets
The diagram shows three lines meeting at a point
The cost of each book is \(12 and the cost of each magazine is\) 5
Write an expression, in terms of \(b\) and \(m\), for the total cost of the books and the magazines
Find the size of an interior angle of a regular 15-sided polygon
Without using a calculator, work out \(2\frac{1}{4} - 1\frac{11}{12}\)
You must show all your working and give your answer as a fraction in its simplest form
Rearrange the formula to write \(x\) in terms of \(V\) and \(y\)
Find the \(n\)th term of each sequence
\(A, B, C\) and \(D\) lie on the circle
\(TAS\) is a tangent to the circle at \(A\)
\(P\), \(Q\) and \(R\) lie on the circle, centre \(O\)
Find the interquartile range of the heights
The box-and-whisker diagram shows information about the heights of some plants
Calculate the shortest distance from \(C\) to \(AB\)
Two mathematically similar solids have volumes \(81 \mathrm{~cm}^3\) and \(24 \mathrm{~cm}^3\)
The height of the smaller solid is \(4.8 \mathrm{~cm}\)
Calculate the height of the larger solid
Solve the equation \(\tan x + 2 = 0\) for \(0^{\circ} \leqslant x \leqslant 360^{\circ}\)
Use set notation to describe the shaded region
The Venn diagram shows the number of elements in each region
The diagram shows a cuboid with a diagonal \(PB\)
Calculate the angle between the diagonal \(PB\) and the base \(ABCD\)
Write \(x^{2} + 8x - 7\) in the form \((x + a)^{2} + b\)
A rectangle has an area of \(150 \mathrm{m}^2\), correct to the nearest square metre
The length of the rectangle is \(22 \mathrm{m}\), correct to the nearest metre
Calculate the upper bound of the width of the rectangle
Give your answer in its simplest form
